I was looking for a bunch of recordings referring to the seven and seven from last year. I must have archived them already. I will have to look there when I get home.

Regards,

Frank R.

----- Original Message ----
From: Lisby &lt;lisby@...&gt;
To: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com
Sent: Monday, February 11, 2008 10:51:59 AM
Subject: Re: [EVP-ITC] New file uploaded to EVP-ITC















Welcome to the great Seven mystery, Nellie. A lot of people get the name/word. I get it constantly. I can&#39;t tell if it an entity or a confirmation word like, &quot;copy,&quot; which I also get a lot. Rosemary also gets Seven and know others on this list have in the past. There is some theory that this is a collective entity that was involved in the ITC bridge group back in the 1980s, but it could just as easily be something the current technicians decided to use to comfort us. We really don&#39;t know at this point.


Ann

On Feb 11, 2008, at 11:45 AM, Nellie Kampmann wrote:

On 11 Feb 2008 16:07:53 -0000, &lt;EVP-ITC@yahoogroups .com&gt; wrote:
&gt; File : /Ann&#39;s files/problemseven0 20408.mp3
&gt; Uploaded by : lisbyfarrum &lt;lisby@earthlink. net&gt;
&gt; Description : My last session appears to have been crashed by the cursing
&gt; entities. Amidst the swearing, &quot;Problem, Seven.&quot; I hear an English accent.

I&#39;m at work where I can&#39;t download the file. However, this message
has me intrigued already. A friend of mine just started experimenting
with a Shack hack last night and also got a message of &quot;seven&quot;. When
she asked for clarification, the response was &quot;you&#39;ll see&quot;. Hmmm.

Nellie

















